In England, in the seven days to 01 November, there were 230,372 new confirmed cases (407.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 October, there were 256,061 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 10% (25,689 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 06 November is 7,877,720 (13,930.5 cases per 100,000 population).
